<P>THE <HI>DROP</HI> and <HI>PILL</HI> OF <HI>Mr.</HI> WARD, CONSIDER'D: AS WELL In re&s;pect to their <HI>Compo&s;ition,</HI> as their <HI>Operation</HI> and <HI>Effects.</HI></P>
<P>WHEREIN, As there is great Rea&s;on to believe, the genuine RECEIPT of both.</P>
<P>IN AN EPISTLE TO Dr. <HI>JAMES JURIN,</HI> Fellow of the COLLEGE of PHYSICIANS, And of the ROYAL SOCIETY: FROM <HI>DANIEL TURNER,</HI> Of the &s;ame COLLEGE of PHYSICIANS in <HI>London.</HI></P>
<P><HI>LONDON:</HI> Printed for JOHN CLARKE, at the <HI>Bible</HI> un|der the <HI>Royal-Exchange,</HI> MDCCXXXV. [Price Six-pence.]</P>
